{"key":"post-10039169","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10039169</id>\n<content>If you used course verm, that's why it's too wet.&amp;nbsp; You're supposed to use medium or fine verm, which holds more water.&amp;nbsp; There's no way to fix them now if they're inoculated, so just hope for the best.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Next time, mix the water and verm well and let it sit for ten minutes.&amp;nbsp; If there's ANY water collecting at the bottom of the bowl at all, pour it out before adding the rice flour.&amp;nbsp; I've actually started making them drier than the 2,1,1 recipe lately and then using 2 to 3 ml of liquid inoculant per half pint jar.&amp;nbsp; This REALLY speeds up colonization.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10039281</next>\n<prev>10039154</prev>\n<first>10038867</first>\n<last>10039318</last>\n<when>1238012338</when>\n<utime>03/25/09 11:18 PM</utime>\n</post>"}